arStrings.szText: Whittling Sanity
Investigate the appearance of demons in the Abahru Canyon
Meet Lorath in Abahru Canyon
I learned at Ked Bardu that a pale man dressed in black has been seen in Abahru Canyon. If that was Elias, a former Horadrim, I fear what lies ahead.
We found a camp littered with merchants slaughtered by demons. Could Elias have summoned them? Lorath and I have a decided to descend into the canyon to look for Elias and the demons there.
Search for Elias in Abahru Canyon
Search for Elias in Abahru Canyon with Lorath
Chasing a lead about a pale man dressed in black seen in Abahru Canyon, I must rendezvous with Lorath and learn what he might have discovered.
Speak with Lorath in Abahru Canyon
Speak with Lorath in Abahru Canyon

Wracked with madness, Genbar the Carver now wields the terrible power to summon demons, bestowed on him by Elias. Only by killing Genbar can we prevent further summonings and return relative safety to the region.
Defeat Genbar in the Rift of a Thousand Eyes
Defeat Genbar
The Abahru Canyon is full of demons. Lorath and I have a decided to descend into the canyon and find the source of the demonic incursions.
Close the Hell rift in Abahru Canyon
Defeat the demons rising from the Hell rift
We have ended the threat Genbar and his demons posed to Ked Bardu. I need to speak to Lorath about our next steps.
Speak with Lorath in the Rift of a Thousand Eyes
Speak with Lorath

The strange house in Abahru Canyon was abandoned but littered with disturbing findings. Its seems the Carver known as Genbar may be responsible for the demonic incursions, but an ancient cave nearby might have the answers we seek.

We have discovered a strange house in the Abahru Canyon that appears untouched by demons, but no sign of any survivors. I doubt we will find any. What happened here? Whose house was this?
